Project: Go Home (2026)
"Get Home Alive." Copyright (c) 2026 branzinosea

1. MISSION STATEMENT
The mission of this project is survival, not monopoly. This Work involves the kinematic repurposing of standard-issue infantry protective gear (Knee/Elbow Pads) into high-pressure hemostatic chamber walls, designed to save lives in Tactical Combat Casualty Care (TCCC) environments.

2. PERMITTED USES & COMMERCIAL FREEDOM
Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this documentation and associated files (the "Work"), to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, and distribute the Work.

Commercial Sales: You are permitted to manufacture and sell physical implementations of this Work (e.g., knee protectors, valves, or high-tensile film) for profit, subject to the "Rigid Interoperability" clause below.

3. MANDATORY CONDITIONS
A. Rigid Interoperability (No Proprietary Lock-in)
To ensure battlefield reliability, all physical implementations must be 100% interchangeable.

Standard Specifications: Any product based on this Work must strictly adhere to the mechanical clearances (0.2–0.3 mm triple sequential V-valve scaling) and docking port geometries defined in the technical manual.

Prohibition of Monopoly: Intentional incompatibility, proprietary locking mechanisms, or encrypted interfaces designed to restrict the use of 3rd-party or DIY components are strictly prohibited under this license.

B. Anti-Patent & Open Intellectual Property

Non-Patentable: No individual or entity shall attempt to patent or claim exclusive intellectual property rights over this design or its derivatives to restrict its free use for saving human lives.

Patent Retaliation: Any entity that files a patent claim based on this Work will have their license terminated immediately and automatically.

C. Mandatory Attribution & Source Transparency

Physical Marking: All physical products must clearly display the text: "DESIGNED BY BRANZINOSEA - PROJECT: GO HOME" on the hardware or its primary packaging to ensure users can verify the source and safety standards.

License Inclusion: The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all copies or substantial portions of the Work.

4. TECHNICAL FOUNDATIONS
This license covers the following core mechanisms:

Constraint-Release Clips: Transforming impact pads into high-pressure latches through leaf spring expansion.

Sequential V-Valves: Springless Cam-Over sliding pressure regulation with 0.2–0.3 mm clearances.

Viscoelastic Gelation: The 'Branzino Pepper' (Thrombin/Chitosan) and moisture-triggered lubrication (PEG) protocol.

